<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Himachal Pradesh</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">Gateway to <em>Mountain Paradise</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Himachal Pradesh, the "Land of Gods," is a breathtaking hill state nestled in the lap of the Himalayas. Known for its misty mountains, cascading waterfalls, alpine meadows and pristine forests, Himachal Pradesh represents nature's most enchanting masterpiece. A destination for adventure seekers and spiritual pilgrims alike, it boasts ancient temples, monasteries and shrines perched on mountain slopes. From the snow-capped peaks of Kinnaur to the apple orchards of Himachal, from the adventure capital Manali to the sacred temples of Chamba, from meditation centers in Dharamshala to the cultural richness of Kullu, Himachal Pradesh offers transformative experiences. The state's harmony with nature, traditional handicrafts, delicious cuisine and warm hospitality make it a sanctuary for those seeking solace in mountains. Adventure sports, trekking, paragliding and skiing attract thrill-seekers, while spiritual seekers find peace in its monasteries and temples.</p>
</section>

